==English==
===Etymology===
By analogy with past tenses and past participles ending in "-unk", such as '''[[drunk]]''' and '''[[sunk]]'''

====Verb form====
'''thunk'''

#An erroneous past tense and [[past participle]] of '''to [[think]]'''.
#:''Who would have thunk it?''

===Etymology===
[[Onomatopoeic]]

====Interjection====
'''thunk!'''

#Representing the sound of a heavy imapct.

===Etymology===
<!--from FOLDOC: http://foldoc.org/?query=thunk&action=Search -->
Claimed by the inventors to be from the supposed past tense, being coined when they realised after much thought (whence "thunk") that the [[type]] of an argument in [[w:ALGOL 60|ALGOL 60]] could be predetermined at [[compile time]]; not, as is sometimes claimed, from the interjection, being the supposed sound made by data hitting the stack or an accumulator

====Noun====
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun-reg}}

#{{computing}} a delayed computation, as in [[functional programming]]
#{{computing}} a [[mapping]] of machine [[data]] from one system[[-specific]] form to another, usually for compatibility reasons, such as from 16-bit addresses to 32-bit to allow a 16-bit program to run on a 32-bit operating system